The Communications Authority has said it will work with the DCI to monitor people who engage in hate speech using social media.Yesterday, chairman Ben Gituku said culprits will be prosecuted.Speaking during an accountability workshop in Nyeri town, he said, &ldquo;Parents should monitor their children because some misuse electronic gadgets, including mobile phones.&rdquo;Nyeri Senator Mutahi Kagwe and US Embassy economic adviser David Pemberton were present.Kagwe urged Kenyans to use technology to fight corruption. Pemberton lauded the Kenyan government for digitising services, adding that it will help improve revenue collection.